SECTION III
L IFE C IRCLE

A CMS, as represented in figure 1 , consists of three phases: information passes through the collection system, where it is transformed in content components, then through the management system, a kind of complex database where components are stored, and, lastly, through the publication system, where information is automatically transformed into publications. The three areas are often largely overlapped and work in strict relation with each other.

