SECTION V
T HE M ANAGEMENT S YSTEM

The management system is responsible for content storage and for the instruments utilized to find and organize the same content and metadata collected in the first phase of the lifecycle. This system comprehends the repository, administration and workflow functions that allow one to know which content the enterprise owns and where it is. In practice the management system permits one to find the answer to any question about content, its collection, or the publications created from it.

