SECTION VIII
G RAPHICAL R EPRESENTATION OF THE S YSTEM

The architectural design of the system explains graphically the system. As its shown in the figure below, the user interacts with the server through the intranet to get access to the system. There are many groups in the system which is greater by the administrator of the system and every group has a parent group and every group has a child as a user because of hierarchical reason. For instance, if parent group represent the Faculty, the child group represent the Department and the member of the department represent the user. I have divided the groups into parent group and child group in order to let the member of the University to respect the hierarchy, for example head of department cant write or communicate directly with the president of the University he should write first to the dean of the faculty etcthis is the way how the system treat the member of the University. The administrations of the system is responsible for creating groups, users and assign the rules, the administration of the system has a easy task to handle because the system is dynamic it means he doesnt have make any changes on the source code of the system while assigning the rules or creating groups.
Figure 4
Fig. 4. System.

