SECTION X
F UNCTIONALITY OF THE S YSTEM

The system has too many functions, only the administrator of the system has total control of the system it means he has the full control. There are too many users and every each user has a password to login to his/ her own profile. A user can be created by the administration of the system; everyone has control of his own profile. There is group, user and every user have a parent as a group and every parent has child as user thats important for the hierarchy within the system.
Figure 6
Fig. 6. Creating group in the system.

