SECTION XII
T ASK M ANAGEMENT T OOL

The task management tool allows the superior member of administration to give task to member of administration. For instance, a Dean of faculty can give task to the head of department and follow and see whether the task given was done. If the task given was done the status of the task will be mentioned by a tick otherwise the status of the task will be mention by a cross in order to evaluate the performance of the member of administration. The task management tool is very important because it help the system to check the work performance of the administration, instructor and giving out a report monthly or annually per department The figure below shows how a task can be given.
Figure 8
Fig. 8. Task management tool.

